        "content": "<p>We have 2 <code>SMul</code>s on functions: <code>((f : α → M) • (g : α → β)) x = f x • g x</code> and <code>((c : M) • (g : α → β)) x = c • g x</code>. Lemmas about both <code>smul</code>s use <code>smul</code> in the name. Should we use some other string in the lemmas about the first <code>smul</code>?</p>",
        "id": 380464065,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1690830798
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Or use <code>const_smul</code> for the latter one as in <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Set.indicator_smul#doc\">docs#Set.indicator_smul</a> and <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=Set.indicator_const_smul#doc\">docs#Set.indicator_const_smul</a> ?</p>",
